            <title>[LUCENE-2966] SegmentReader.doCommit should be sync&apos;d; norms methods need not be sync&apos;d</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/LUCENE-2966</link>
                <project id="12310110" key="LUCENE">Lucene - Core</project>
                        <description>&lt;p&gt;I fixed the failure in TestNRTThreads, but in the process tripped an assert because SegmentReader.doCommit isn&apos;t sync&apos;d.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;So I sync&apos;d it, but I don&apos;t think the norms APIs need to be sync&apos;d &amp;#8211; we populate norms up front and then never change them.  Un-sync&apos;ing them is important so that in the NRT case calling IW.commit doesn&apos;t block searches trying to pull norms.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Also some small code refactoring.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
